The department made the announcement on Friday evening, adding that lower oil prices contributed to the decrease. JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Energy has announced that the fuel price will decrease by between 75 and 95 cents a litre from the stroke of midnight next Wednesday. The department made the announcement on Friday evening, adding that lower oil prices contributed to the decrease. The price of 93 and 95 unleaded petrol will go down by 96 and 95 cents a litre respectively. Diesel will decrease by 75 cents.